  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::PixeLadder.SimpleTooltip.TooltipTrigger
  title: Difficulty
  content: "Defines the agression levels of SCPs and saving functionality.\n\n<color=green>SAFE</color>
    - The game can be saved any time. However, as in the case of SCP Objects, a Safe
    classification doesn't mean that handling it doesn't pose a threat. \n\n<color=yellow>EUCLID</color>
    - In Euclid difficulty, saving is only allowed at specific locations marked by
    lit up computer screens. Euclid-class objects are inherently unpredictable, so
    that reliable containment is not always possible.\n\n<color=red>KETER</color>
    - Keter-class objects are considered the most dangerous ones in Foundation containment.
    The same can be said for this difficulty level: the SCPs are more aggressive,
    and you have only one life - when you die, the game is over.  "
  icon: {fileID: 8137855467138495615, guid: faff25acf1213294b97dac5671330ff0, type: 3}
  overrideStyle: 0
  titleColor: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  iconColor: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  backgroundColor: {r: 0.1, g: 0.1, b: 0.1, a: 0.95}
  showOutline: 1
  outlineColor: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  overrideLayout: 0
  positionMode: 0
  anchorPosition: 0
  additionalOffset: {x: 0, y: 0}
  overrideSize: 0
  maxWidth: 350
  overrideTimer: 0
  hoverDelay: 1
  onTooltipShow:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  onTooltipHide:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
